---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Morocco Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/morocco/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/portugal' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'moroccoFit', header: 'Morocco Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD 3,500-5,000/mo', moroccoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD 4,100-5,900/mo', moroccoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD 3,200-4,600/mo', moroccoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD 3,000-4,400/mo', moroccoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Moroccan Local (Saham, RMA)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'MAD 800-2,500/mo', moroccoFit: 'Basic Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MAD 3,200-5,000', annual: 'MAD 38,400-60,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MAD 4,400-6,700', annual: 'MAD 52,800-80,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MAD 6,000-9,000', annual: 'MAD 72,000-108,000' },
  { category: 'Moroccan Private (Clinique)', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'MAD 300-800/visit' },
  { category: 'Moroccan Public', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'Limited access' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Morocco 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Morocco. Marrakech magic, affordable living, good private healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Morocco"
  subheadline="Morocco offers exotic charm, affordable living, good private healthcare, and proximity to Europe—a popular retirement destination for French and British expats."
  heroImage="/images/countries/morocco-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Morocco</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco combines exotic appeal with accessibility—just 3 hours from Europe, culturally rich, affordable, and welcoming to expats. Marrakech and Essaouira attract art lovers; Tangier has literary heritage; Agadir offers beach life. French is widely spoken, easing communication.
  </p>

  <p>
    Marrakech provides vibrant cultural living with riads and souks. Essaouira offers bohemian coastal atmosphere. Tangier combines Mediterranean and Atlantic. Agadir is beach-focused and modern. Fes has authentic medina life. Each city offers distinct character for retirement.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good private in major cities; limited rural</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic/French; English in tourist areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MAD 10,000-25,000/month (~$1,000-2,500); low</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean north; desert south</li>
      <li><strong>Europe Access:</strong> 3 hours from Paris/London</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Exotic, affordable, culturally rich</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Morocco's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco has developing healthcare with good private sector in major cities. Casablanca has the best facilities—Cheikh Khalifa Hospital, Clinique Badr. Marrakech and Rabat have adequate private clinics. French-trained doctors are common. Quality is good for routine and moderate complexity.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is free but crowded and underfunded—not recommended for expats. For complex care, evacuation to France or Spain is common (1-2 hour flight). International insurance with European coverage is essential for seniors.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">France as Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Many Morocco expats use France as healthcare backup—3 hours from Casablanca. Complex cases often transfer to French hospitals. Ensure international insurance covers France for this scenario. Morocco's private care handles most needs; France provides safety net for serious conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco offers flexible options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>90-Day Visa-Free + Extensions</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities (US, UK, EU) get 90 days visa-free. Extensions possible at police stations. Some retirees do "visa runs" to Spain (ferry from Tangier) for extended informal stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Card (Carte de Séjour)</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term residence—requires proof of income, accommodation, health insurance. Valid 1 year initially, renewable. Process is bureaucratic but achievable. Most serious retirees pursue this after initial 90-day experience.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Owning property supports residence applications. Morocco allows foreign property ownership. Many retirees buy riads in Marrakech/Essaouira as both home and investment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Morocco:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence card:</strong> Health insurance typically required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Private coverage essential (public limited)</li>
    <li><strong>France access:</strong> Include coverage for French evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>Spain option:</strong> Tangier area can access Spanish healthcare</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Morocco</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for Morocco seniors. Local insurers have age limits and coverage gaps. Ensure plan covers: Moroccan private clinics, evacuation to France/Spain, and worldwide emergency. Casablanca has best healthcare; elsewhere plan for travel or evacuation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Morocco, international coverage with European access is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Morocco</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, France coverage included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> French company, excellent Morocco/France coordination</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Mediterranean region pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with France evacuation access essential for Morocco.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Morocco are low given affordable local healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Moroccan private care is cheap; high deductible for serious issues</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations MAD 300-500; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Morocco + France/Spain focused rather than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Local supplement:</strong> Saham/RMA for routine + international for serious</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: French Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,800/month pension. Buying riad in Marrakech. French-speaking environment.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Carte de séjour. AXA Global with France coverage. Uses Clinique du Sud locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> AXA ~MAD 3,800/month (~€350). Cultural immersion with French backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension £2,500/month. Retiring to Essaouira coast.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both with UK/France coverage. Uses Casablanca for specialist care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~MAD 9,000/month combined (~£830). Bohemian beach lifestyle; excellent backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: American Artist, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month pension + art sales. Seeking exotic inspiration. Tangier.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Spain access (ferry to Tarifa). Uses Tangier private clinics.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~MAD 4,200/month (~$420). Creative haven with Spain healthcare option.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Morocco safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—one of Africa's most stable countries. Tourist areas are well-policed. Petty crime exists (pickpocketing in medinas). Terrorism risk is low. Women may experience more harassment than Europe but serious crime is rare. Standard travel precautions apply.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need French to live in Morocco?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely helpful. French is widely spoken in business, healthcare, and educated circles. English works in tourist areas but French opens many more doors. Arabic is official but French suffices for most expat needs. Consider French lessons before moving.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the Carte de Séjour process like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Bureaucratic but achievable. Requires: passport, proof of income, accommodation, health insurance, police clearance. Apply at local prefecture. Process takes 2-6 months. Renewal is simpler after first year. Many retirees use immigration consultants to navigate paperwork.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Morocco healthcare compare to Europe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Private care in major cities is adequate for most needs—not European standard but acceptable. French-trained doctors are common. Equipment is modern in good clinics. Complex cases benefit from French evacuation. Better than most developing countries; below European standards for complex care.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with France evacuation coverage for Morocco.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Moroccan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
